*I*  *LOVE* *THIS* *PLACE*  Forget SILVIAS (oh my! so expensive, so tourist) if you want REAL soul food.  It is not fancy.  It is not full of what we might call ambiance  - BUT - The food is outstanding. The flavor is delicious.  The attitude - well - there isn't one.  While there aren't many seats, I joined a table (admittedly the gentleman was a tiny bit shocked when I asked, but happily made space for me).  I understand there are seats upstairs.  It is a steam table situation - choose what you want and get it weighed.  Everything from salads to sides to meats.  Yams, and greens, and hams, and chickens and....sooogooooood.  I always try to bring NYC visitors here- real old skool NYC.

It was my first time going to this location on 125th st. I usually go to the one on Fredrick Douglas Blvd. It was 5:30pm. The ham was completely black, the smothered chicken was definitely from the day before because it was hard, the salmon looked bad, the collard greens (what was left in the pan) were shriveled up stems sitting in a pool of juice. All of this while the chef/cook was walking back and forth monitering the food for replacements. So I waited for a bit to see if he was going to refill anything....... Yup you guessed it. He did not. Instead he went to the front to finish his conversation with the cashier. The only thing good that I have to say about this place is the salad bar was right. But I'll never go there again. Its back to Fredrick Douglas location for me. Its a huge difference.

I stopped in here on a whim because I was hungry. I loaded up a styrofoam container with chicken, a few samplings of different salads and, of course, Mac 'n cheese and collard greens. The only thing I was disappointed in was the Mac 'n cheese, but probably because it wasn't as fresh as the other dishes.  This place is no frills with solid, good soul food. There are certain dishes I wouldn't touch (if you're into pigs' feet, knock yourself out!) but I look forward to coming back and trying something new.  Be prepared to pay per pound.
